{{Infobox Organization |name = Lamplighters Yeshivah |image = |image_border = |size = |caption = Lamplighters Yeshivah |map = |msize = |mcaption = |abbreviation = |formation = November 2009 |extinction = |type = |status = |purpose = |headquarters = |location = Crown Heights, Brooklyn |membership = |language = |leader_title = |leader_name = |main_organ = |parent_organization = |affiliations = |num_staff = |num_volunteers = |budget = |website = {{URL|http://www.lamplightersyeshivah.com/}} }}
'''Lamplighters Yeshivah''' is a [[Jewish]] [[Montessori]]-style school for Jewish children located in [[Crown Heights, Brooklyn]].<ref name="lamp home">[http://www.lamplightersyeshivah.com/#! Lamplighters Yeshivah Homepage. Accessed February 21, 2014.]</ref><ref name="lamp NYT">[http://nytimes.com/2014/02/22/education/montessori-schools-surge-in-popularity-among-new-generation-of-jewish-parents.html Yee, Vivian. Montessori Schools Surge in Popularity Among New Generation of Jewish Parents. ''The New York Times''. February 21, 2014. Accessed February 21, 2014.]</ref><ref name="lamp Vos">[http://www.vosizneias.com/122462/2013/01/24/brooklyn-ny-new-chabad-yeshiva-emphasizes-secular-religious-studies-in-student-curriculum/ Vos Iz Neis. Accessed February 21, 2014.]</ref><ref name="lamp DNA">[http://www.dnainfo.com/new-york/20130124/crown-heights/new-crown-heights-yeshiva-guiding-light-for-jewish-education Sharp, Sonja. New Crown Heights Yeshiva a Guiding Light for Jewish Education. ''DNAinfo.com''. January 24, 2013. Accessed February 21, 2014.] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140305225307/http://www.dnainfo.com/new-york/20130124/crown-heights/new-crown-heights-yeshiva-guiding-light-for-jewish-education |date=March 5, 2014 }}</ref><ref name="lamp sis">[http://blogs.forward.com/sisterhood-blog/169090/women-behind-creative-school-in-crown-heights/ Trappler Spielman, Sara. Women Behind Creative School in Crown Heights. The Sisterhood. ''The Jewish Daily Forward''. January 11, 2013. Forward.com. Accessed February 21, 2014.]</ref>
== Background == Lamplighters Yeshivah is one of the 47 plus [[Jewish]] [[Montessori]]-style [[Hebrew day school]]s or yeshivas in the United States. Lamplighters is located in [[Crown Heights, Brooklyn|Crown Heights]], [[Brooklyn]] and is catered to parents from the local [[Chabad]] [[Hasidic]] community.<ref name="lamp NYT"/><ref>[http://www.bkreader.com/2014/02/religious-diversity-freedom-and-choice-emphasized-at-jewish-montessori-schools-a-relatively-new-model-growing-in-popularity/ "'DIVERSITY, FREEDOM AND CHOICE’ EMPHASIZED AT JEWISH MONTESSORIS, A RELATIVELY NEW, GROWING EDUCATIONAL MODEL."] February 23, 2014. ''The Brooklyn Reader''. Accessed May 25, 2014.</ref>
The school was founded in November 2009, with just four families.<ref>[http://www.lamplightersyeshivah.com/#!about_us/c1q1e About Us. Lamplighters Yeshivah. Accessed February 21, 2014.]</ref> As of the 2016-17 school year, the school has expanded to 131 students in eight classes: two primary, three lower elementary and two upper elementary.
The executive director of Lamplighters is Yocheved Sidof. The Heads of School are Moshe and Rivkah Schack.
The name "Lamplighters" was chosen for the school based on the Hasidic teaching<ref>[http://www.chabad.org/library/article_cdo/aid/2183/jewish/The-Lamplighter.htm The Lamplighter. ''Chabad.org''. Accessed February 21, 2014.]</ref> that each person can better the world and "transform darkness into light".<ref name="lamp sis"/>
== Educational style == Lamplighters incorporates both Jewish and general topics in their curriculum. Teaching methods are heavily influenced by Montessori educational methods. Lessons often blend traditional Jewish topics with general Montessori activities.<ref name="lamp NYT"/><ref>[http://www.thejewishweek.com/news/national-news/jewish-montessori-becomes-movement "Jewish Motessori Becomes Movement."] ''The Jewish Week''. Accessed May 25, 2014.</ref>
