{{Taxobox | image = | image_width = 220px | image_caption = ''Psilocybe keralensis'' | regnum = [[Fungi]] | divisio = [[Basidiomycota]] | classis = [[Agaricomycetes]] | ordo = [[Agaricales]] | familia = [[Strophariaceae]] | genus = ''[[Psilocybe]]'' | species = '''''P. keralensis''''' | binomial = ''Psilocybe keralensis'' | binomial_authority = K.A. Thomas, Manim. and [[Gastón Guzmán|Guzmán]] (2002) }}
'''''Psilocybe keralensis''''' is a species of [[psilocybin mushroom]] in the family [[Strophariaceae]]. It contains the compounds [[psilocybin]] and [[psilocin]]. ''Psilocybe keralensis'' is known only from [[Kerala]], [[India]].<ref name="Thomas"/> It is in the ''[[Psilocybe fagicola]]'' complex with ''Psilocybe fagicola'', ''[[Psilocybe oaxacana]]'', ''[[Psilocybe banderillensis]]'', ''[[Psilocybe columbiana]]'', ''[[Psilocybe herrerae]]'', ''[[Psilocybe neoxalapensis]]'', and ''[[Psilocybe teofiloi]]''.<ref name=Guzman2012/>
